item.title: Anyone have a tip on getting the unrenamed to compile?
item.dc:creator: @sdouble sdouble
item.description:
@sdouble wrote:

Yeah, I’m just going to mess with it renamed. No big deal. Thanks anyway.

I dumped all of their methods to a file (boat.txt of course) and started going through it and noticed a lot of duplicates.

This is the client without deobbing

public static final void client.main(java.lang.String[])
public final void client.init()
final void client.c(int)
final void client.c(byte)
private final void client.b(boolean)
static final int client.a(int,byte[],int)
static final int client.a(int,boolean,int)
static final boolean client.a(hb,byte)
private final void client.a(int,int)
static final void client.a(pe,pe,boolean,int)
final void client.d(byte)
public static void client.e(int)
final void client.f(byte)
final void client.h(byte)
private final void client.i(byte)
private static final void client.j(byte)

and here is the deobbed/renamed version

public static void client.main(java.lang.String[])
public void client.init()
public void client.method32(int)
public static void client.method36(int)
public static boolean client.method37(Class58_Sub6_Sub8,byte)
public void client.method22(byte)
public void client.method38(boolean)
public void client.method28(byte)
public static void client.method39(Class46,Class46,boolean,int)
public void client.method40(int,int)
public void client.method41(byte)
public static void client.method42(byte)
public void client.method19(byte)
public static int client.method43(int,boolean,int)
public void client.method34(byte)
public static int client.method44(int,byte[],int)

I would rather use renamed than look at that crap anyhow.
